"{\"uid\": \"myrepublica.nagariknetwork.com-news-olympian-phupu-feted\", \"text\": \"Subscribe Now  KATHMANDU, Jan 11:\\u00a0Nepal Judo Association (NJA) on Tuesday feted judoka Phupu Lhamu Khatri who represented Nepal in the Rio Olympics 2016 held in August.Phupu, the wild card entry from Nepal, had competed for full four minutes in her first bout against Cuban opponent Maricet Espinosa in women's U-63 kg category.Phupu was rewarded with Rs 25,000 for her very feat as per NJA's declaration before leaving for Brazil.She also became the first Nepali judoka to compete for full time in a bout.Menwhile, Phupu's coach Debu Thapa was also rewarded with Rs 10,000.National Sports Council Member Secretary Keshav Kumar Bista rewarded them.Meanwhile, NJA also rewarded the silver medalists of 10th Asian Cadet and 17th Asian Junior Judo Championship held in India in September last year.Coincidentally, Phupu was one among them to secure second place finish in junior category.Manita was the other player to achieve similar feat in women's cadet U-57 kg section.Both of them were rewarded with Rs 10,000 each.  Ballot Box Revolt: What RSP's breakthrough victory...  Warning, Threat or Opportunity? Nepal's major part...  Granary in crisis: Water politics leave Madhesh pa...  \\\"China stands ready to work with Nepal to carry forward the traditional friendship, deepen practical cooperation and advance bilateral relations\\\", read the statement.  Building Nepal's Digital Future  Fuel shortages in Nepal: A hidden threat to health a...  Second Innings of Balen and Gagan  Who will become Balen's climate pilot?  Three \\\"S\\\" factors-sulabhata (availability), sangat (peer influence), and siko (imitation)-are driving Madhesh's youth toward drug addiction.<...  Three \\\"S\\\" factors-sulabhata (availability), sangat (peer influence), and siko (imitation)-are driving Madhesh's youth toward drug addiction.<...  ANFA CEO Indraman Tuladhar said the ANFA submitted all necessary documents regardi